WEBVTT

00:04.833 --> 00:06.041
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:06.125 --> 00:07.208
- [screams]

00:07.291 --> 00:08.458
- [in distorted voice]
Dory.

00:08.541 --> 00:10.041
- [screams]

00:10.125 --> 00:11.916
- [in distorted voice]
Dory.

00:12.000 --> 00:13.875
- [screaming]

00:13.958 --> 00:15.250
- Dory?

00:15.333 --> 00:17.000
The waitress is asking
for your order.

00:17.083 --> 00:19.416
Can you please just say "eggs"
or something?

00:19.500 --> 00:20.500
You're scaring me.

00:20.583 --> 00:22.083
<i>[Christmas carol playing]</i>

00:22.166 --> 00:23.333
- She's back.

00:24.333 --> 00:25.458
- Hey.

00:26.333 --> 00:28.458
- Hmm? Oh.

00:29.291 --> 00:31.000
Sorry.
- That's okay.

00:31.083 --> 00:32.458
- Could I just have...

00:33.541 --> 00:35.125
Some ice cream?

00:36.208 --> 00:37.375
Neapolitan.

00:37.458 --> 00:39.583
- You got it.
- Just ice cream?

00:39.666 --> 00:41.500
I mean--sorry.

00:42.333 --> 00:44.625
That's so fun! I love that
you ordered that, girl.

00:44.708 --> 00:47.500
Oh, that's cute. Ice cream.
[laughs]

00:47.583 --> 00:49.583
[whispering]
She was brainwashed.

00:49.666 --> 00:51.291
<i>- ♪ Oh, but dear ♪</i>

00:51.375 --> 00:54.541
<i>♪ The sky is low, watch ♪</i>

00:54.625 --> 00:55.791
<i>♪ Fluent sea men... ♪</i>

00:55.875 --> 00:58.083
- So Dor, how you feeling?

00:58.166 --> 01:01.000
We can go home right away,
or maybe we could go

01:01.083 --> 01:03.625
to the police first
and then leave.

01:04.500 --> 01:05.583
- Yeah.

01:06.375 --> 01:09.041
Yeah, that makes sense.
- Yeah.

01:09.125 --> 01:11.625
- Yeah, we should report it.

01:11.708 --> 01:15.458
He can't do this to anyone
ever again.

01:15.541 --> 01:16.666
- Okay. Great.

01:16.750 --> 01:18.541
So we'll, uh, go to
the police,

01:18.625 --> 01:20.333
and then you can sleep
in the car

01:20.416 --> 01:22.583
on the drive back to the city
if you need to.

01:27.250 --> 01:29.916
- What do you guys live for?

01:31.208 --> 01:32.625
- What's up? What?

01:33.541 --> 01:34.666
- Like...

01:35.791 --> 01:37.791
Like, what gets you up...

01:37.875 --> 01:39.833
in the morning?

01:39.916 --> 01:41.666
- I love acting.

01:41.750 --> 01:42.916
- Hmm.

01:44.458 --> 01:45.666
Well, um--

01:45.750 --> 01:48.583
what do you love about acting?

01:50.000 --> 01:53.375
- Okay, well,
I fundamentally believe

01:53.458 --> 01:57.166
that watching celebrities talk
in the form of lines

01:57.250 --> 01:59.166
can help people
cope with life and, like,

01:59.250 --> 02:01.250
honestly, for me,
that feels noble and, like,

02:01.333 --> 02:03.166
a reason to get up
every morning.

02:03.250 --> 02:04.458
- Hmm.

02:07.375 --> 02:09.000
What about you, Elliott?

02:11.541 --> 02:13.250
- What about me, what, honey?

02:13.333 --> 02:16.416
- What...gives you meaning?

02:18.291 --> 02:22.166
- Honestly, lately,
it's been all about, like,

02:22.250 --> 02:24.541
connecting with the unexpected.

02:24.625 --> 02:26.625
Like, my work literally
has me engaging

02:26.708 --> 02:29.541
with the kind of people
we would all regularly avoid,

02:29.625 --> 02:32.375
which I guess is just
kind of exciting for me.

02:32.458 --> 02:34.500
You know,
to represent the people

02:34.583 --> 02:37.041
I have a hard time loving.
It's a challenge.

02:37.125 --> 02:40.000
But it's also kind of
a fascinating place

02:40.083 --> 02:41.875
to be in your life, and...

02:41.958 --> 02:43.375
you know, to be honest,

02:43.458 --> 02:47.000
I don't know if I believe
anything that I just said.

02:49.208 --> 02:50.791
- Drew?

02:50.875 --> 02:53.416
- [sighs]
Um...

02:53.500 --> 02:55.750
yeah, uh, you just do.

02:55.833 --> 02:58.083
Okay? You just--
you just get up.

02:58.166 --> 02:59.750
Because you have to.

02:59.833 --> 03:02.333
All right, look, I know, Dory,
that you're going through...

03:02.416 --> 03:05.041
and have been going through
some sort of...

03:05.125 --> 03:07.625
unique trauma or something,

03:07.708 --> 03:09.708
but generally,
we have it very easy.

03:09.791 --> 03:12.083
Or do you think starving people
in other countries

03:12.166 --> 03:14.166
ask themselves these questions?

03:14.250 --> 03:15.500
Do you think
that our ancestors did?

03:15.583 --> 03:17.000
No! They just got up,
all right?

03:17.083 --> 03:18.333
They got up,
and then they painted

03:18.416 --> 03:20.166
their little caves
or made tools

03:20.250 --> 03:23.166
out of a saber-toothed tiger
tooth or whatever, okay?

03:23.250 --> 03:25.125
They just...they just did.

03:25.208 --> 03:27.000
They didn't think about it.

03:27.083 --> 03:29.166
They just got up.

03:31.333 --> 03:32.625
- I just...

03:32.708 --> 03:35.791
I don't even know what
I'm gonna do when I get home.

03:37.250 --> 03:38.416
It's like...

03:41.208 --> 03:43.541
Who am I even gonna be?

03:48.875 --> 03:51.416
- You're just gonna be Dory,

03:51.500 --> 03:53.000
Dory.

03:57.500 --> 04:00.458
- I just don't know
if that's a good thing to be.

04:00.541 --> 04:02.625
- Dor, you're great.

04:03.541 --> 04:05.500
- I'm a hazard.

04:09.625 --> 04:12.208
- Dor, I think you just
have to really remember

04:12.291 --> 04:14.166
that, like, you didn't want

04:14.250 --> 04:16.041
any of this to happen,
you know?

04:16.125 --> 04:19.000
- Yeah, most of this stuff
happened to us.

04:19.083 --> 04:21.166
You know, we--we didn't have
any real agency

04:21.250 --> 04:22.291
at any given moment.

04:22.375 --> 04:23.958
You know,
we have to start taking

04:24.041 --> 04:27.250
more responsibility
for how little responsibility

04:27.333 --> 04:29.250
we've actually had
in our lives.

04:30.250 --> 04:32.416
- I think there's something...

04:32.500 --> 04:34.458
wrong with me.

04:34.541 --> 04:36.333
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

04:36.416 --> 04:40.000
He saw something in me,

04:40.083 --> 04:42.125
And I'm just terrified that...

04:43.458 --> 04:45.666
That there's this person...

04:45.750 --> 04:48.500
deep down inside of me that...

04:50.375 --> 04:53.208
I don't fully understand.

04:55.208 --> 04:58.291
And that I cannot trust.

05:00.625 --> 05:04.125
I think I made
all these things happen.

05:08.125 --> 05:10.958
- Well, to be fair, girl...
[chuckles]

05:11.041 --> 05:12.750
your 20s are all about...

05:14.166 --> 05:15.458
Th-that.

05:16.791 --> 05:18.250
- What?
- [stammers] I don't know!

05:18.333 --> 05:20.083
I'm sorry, Drew.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

05:20.166 --> 05:21.708
At least I tried
to say something, okay?

05:21.791 --> 05:23.041
That was noble.
You're just sitting there

05:23.125 --> 05:24.291
with the fucking half and half

05:24.375 --> 05:26.250
like you're...
making butter.

05:26.333 --> 05:27.708
- Okay, Dory.

05:27.791 --> 05:30.333
Is there something
that you're trying to tell us?

05:31.583 --> 05:33.500
- You never should've
looked for me.

05:33.583 --> 05:34.750
- [gasps]

05:35.833 --> 05:38.375
- Okay, yay, ice cream.

05:38.458 --> 05:40.833
Is there anything else
I can get you?

05:46.250 --> 05:47.375
- Hmm.

05:49.666 --> 05:51.750
Yeah, it's not the same.

05:52.583 --> 05:54.416
- Uh, Dory.
- Dor...

05:54.500 --> 05:56.125
- Where is she going?

05:56.208 --> 05:57.583
- I can--
I honestly can bring her

05:57.666 --> 05:59.416
literally anything else.

05:59.500 --> 06:02.750
- You're doing beautiful work.
It's not about you.

06:02.833 --> 06:04.291
- Thank you.

06:05.666 --> 06:08.083
- Okay, honestly, this is mean,
but she sounds like an idiot.

06:08.166 --> 06:09.375
That was like
a conversation you have

06:09.458 --> 06:11.916
with someone in college.
[laughs]

06:12.000 --> 06:14.958
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:15.041 --> 06:22.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:31.291 --> 06:33.666
<i>- Are you the...the twink?</i>

06:33.750 --> 06:35.583
<i>- But you can call me "Chip."</i>

06:35.666 --> 06:37.875
<i>I'm your best friend.</i>

06:40.625 --> 06:41.958
- [sobs]

06:42.041 --> 06:43.750
<i>Stephanie.</i>

06:43.833 --> 06:46.416
<i>- Well, Stephanie,</i>
<i>I'm thinking...</i>

06:46.500 --> 06:49.875
<i>we go out into the world</i>
<i>together.</i>

06:49.958 --> 06:52.625
<i>I need you to trust me.</i>

06:52.708 --> 06:53.875
- [screams]

06:53.958 --> 06:55.416
- I went, like, very far

06:55.500 --> 06:56.875
[phone buzzing]
with women.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.333
- How come
I didn't know that?

06:58.416 --> 06:59.666
- In middle school.
- [sighs] God.

06:59.750 --> 07:02.333
Why is my brother calling me?

07:02.416 --> 07:03.500
Hey.

07:04.916 --> 07:06.625
Why do you need to know?

07:07.583 --> 07:10.125
I already told you where I am.

07:10.208 --> 07:13.666
Yeah, I'm at a motel.
It's called "The Babyfoot Inn."

07:13.750 --> 07:15.750
It's like
the only motel in town.

07:16.958 --> 07:20.208
Why are you so concerned
about where I am these days?

07:21.958 --> 07:24.166
Okay, weirdo.

07:24.250 --> 07:25.375
Bye.

07:26.916 --> 07:28.750
Everyone has lost their minds.

07:28.833 --> 07:30.625
- I know.
- I know.

07:34.000 --> 07:36.166
- Is this cashmere? It--

07:36.250 --> 07:37.458
- It's wool.

07:40.458 --> 07:43.458
- Tasteful tattoos.
They're so sweet.

07:46.791 --> 07:48.208
[inhales]

07:48.291 --> 07:50.375
Chip, love, please,
talk to me.

07:50.458 --> 07:53.375
I mean, you--it's--
it is hurting my heart

07:53.458 --> 07:55.541
to get this cold treatment.

07:56.708 --> 07:59.291
- I'm just in shock, okay?

08:00.375 --> 08:03.875
I just need to process this
on my own time.

08:03.958 --> 08:06.166
- I understand, but I tried.

08:06.250 --> 08:10.875
I tried my very best
to raise you from a distance.

08:12.458 --> 08:16.083
When you were a toddler,
I made candy bars,

08:16.166 --> 08:19.125
and, you know, I cut a hole
in the middle,

08:19.208 --> 08:21.208
and I sent them to Richard
to give to you.

08:21.291 --> 08:25.083
And then when I was at home,
I would imagine that...

08:25.166 --> 08:27.708
you were eating the bar
while I was at home,

08:27.791 --> 08:29.250
eating the hole.

08:29.333 --> 08:32.000
And together, then, that meant
that we were eating...

08:32.083 --> 08:35.083
the entire candy bar.

08:39.333 --> 08:41.125
- There they are.

08:42.666 --> 08:44.000
Teens.

08:48.750 --> 08:51.166
- Yoo-hoo! Boys!

08:52.000 --> 08:53.750
You like fire?

08:55.125 --> 08:56.791
- Babe, you know,
you don't need to tip.

08:56.875 --> 08:58.916
Not outside the city.

08:59.000 --> 09:01.416
- Yes, you do.
You always have to tip.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.250
- No, but I think in
like rural towns like this,

09:03.333 --> 09:04.708
you can cap it at a 5%

09:04.791 --> 09:07.291
because a dollar
goes a long way here.

09:07.375 --> 09:09.750
- Where the hell is Dory?

09:09.833 --> 09:12.291
- Wait, wasn't the car parked,
like, right there?

09:12.375 --> 09:14.666
Is the car gone?

09:16.125 --> 09:17.458
- Oh, no.
- Shit!

09:17.541 --> 09:19.416
- Dory? Dory!
- No!

09:20.541 --> 09:22.541
- Oh...my God!

09:22.625 --> 09:24.083
Did she go back to him?

09:24.166 --> 09:25.583
Did she go back to the twink?

09:25.666 --> 09:27.125
- Ow, my knee!

09:27.208 --> 09:29.375
Oh, twisted my knee!

09:29.458 --> 09:30.708
Oh, shit.

09:30.791 --> 09:32.541
- Mom?

09:32.625 --> 09:34.125
- Shoot!

09:34.208 --> 09:35.416
He saw me.

09:35.500 --> 09:36.875
I'm sorry, he saw me.

09:36.958 --> 09:41.666
- Mom! God damn it!
You screw up everything!

09:43.458 --> 09:44.833
- What are you doing here?

09:44.916 --> 09:46.833
- Hi. Oops, sorry.

09:46.916 --> 09:48.583
Are you--
are you Andrew?

09:48.666 --> 09:50.083
- Yes.
- I'm sorry.

09:50.166 --> 09:51.250
I'm supposed
to give this to you.

09:51.333 --> 09:52.833
I don't--sorry.

09:52.916 --> 09:55.041
- [whispering]
Why is his family here?

09:55.125 --> 09:57.375
- [whispering]
I don't know.

