- [laughs]

12:03.041 --> 12:04.458
- Portia, could you hold this?
- What?

12:04.541 --> 12:06.458
Can you hold the key--
hold the keyboard?

12:07.458 --> 12:08.916
- [whispering]
What's happening?

12:09.000 --> 12:10.583
- Uh...
- [laughs]

12:10.666 --> 12:13.125
- Can I--can we talk,
um, about this

12:13.208 --> 12:15.458
maybe somewhere away
from everybody really quick?

12:15.541 --> 12:18.083
- Speak up!
I can't hear you say "yes"!

12:18.166 --> 12:19.791
- Speak up!
- [stammers] Can we just...

12:19.875 --> 12:21.833
please go over here somewhere
and just talk about this

12:21.916 --> 12:23.375
in private really quick.
- No, no!

12:23.458 --> 12:26.208
What do you want to say?
Just say it here. Say it.

12:26.291 --> 12:29.458
Say it here so it can be a part
of this magical moment.

12:29.541 --> 12:31.375
- C--Cindy...

12:31.458 --> 12:32.791
please.

12:32.875 --> 12:35.625
please, please, please,
please-please-please,

12:35.708 --> 12:37.583
don't do this.

12:37.666 --> 12:39.000
- He said "yes"!

12:39.083 --> 12:40.666
[all cheering]

12:40.750 --> 12:44.083
- No! No! No, no, no!
I did not say "yes"!

12:44.166 --> 12:45.333
- Yes, you did!
- No, I didn't!

12:45.416 --> 12:46.375
Everyone needs to understand

12:46.458 --> 12:47.666
I did not say "yes."

12:47.750 --> 12:49.208
- Honey, just say "yes"
to her.

12:49.291 --> 12:51.166
- I did not ask for this!

12:51.250 --> 12:54.583
Okay, Cindy, I still don't know

12:54.666 --> 12:56.833
how much
that I actually love you.

12:56.916 --> 12:59.458
I'm so sorry.
- Oh, no, no, no.

12:59.541 --> 13:01.500
- I'm using you!
- No!

13:01.583 --> 13:03.333
- I'm using you
to try and get over Dory.

13:03.416 --> 13:04.708
- What!? No!

13:04.791 --> 13:06.000
- I'm addicted to her!

13:06.083 --> 13:07.625
[Cindy crying]
Okay?

13:07.708 --> 13:11.375
I'm addicted to a brainwashed,
psychotic murderer!

13:11.458 --> 13:13.833
I can't stop
thinking about her!

13:13.916 --> 13:15.625
I'm not well!

13:15.708 --> 13:17.166
Okay? Neither are you!

13:17.250 --> 13:19.083
Or you! Or you!

13:19.166 --> 13:22.083
And Merry Merry Land
is not merry!

13:22.166 --> 13:23.750
- [sobbing]
Oh, no, no.

13:23.833 --> 13:26.083
- And I'm still in love
with Dory.

13:31.583 --> 13:34.458
- Aah!
[sobbing]

13:35.083 --> 13:37.375
- Broad strokes, boys.
Come on, broad strokes.

13:37.458 --> 13:38.666
Don't be stingy.

13:38.750 --> 13:40.708
I want every inch
of this place soaked.

13:40.791 --> 13:43.625
If you run out, there's more
where that came from.

13:43.708 --> 13:45.000
And smile!

13:45.083 --> 13:47.583
You're supposed
to be having fun!

13:50.125 --> 13:52.125
- Good-bye, floral runner.

13:53.208 --> 13:54.416
Good-bye, wig.

13:55.416 --> 13:57.250
[grunts]
The portrait.

14:02.875 --> 14:04.125
- Chip.

14:04.208 --> 14:06.375
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:06.458 --> 14:07.708
- Stephanie?

14:07.791 --> 14:09.500
- Dory.

14:09.583 --> 14:12.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:12.083 --> 14:13.416
- Hey!

14:14.958 --> 14:17.416
Hey! Hey! Wait!

14:17.500 --> 14:24.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:25.125 --> 14:26.458
Come on, Chip.

14:26.541 --> 14:29.041
I'm not gonna hurt you.
I just want to talk.

14:29.125 --> 14:36.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:38.041 --> 14:39.208
Ha!

14:47.791 --> 14:48.958
- Drewbie?

14:50.041 --> 14:51.958
Was that your girlfriend?

14:52.041 --> 14:54.000
- Can you guys just please
give me some space?

14:54.083 --> 14:55.666
I don't want to talk about this
right now.

14:55.750 --> 14:58.625
- No, I'm just wondering,
where did you guys meet?

14:58.708 --> 15:00.166
- Nowhere.

15:00.250 --> 15:01.625
- Okay, Drew, when I went
through your bag

15:01.708 --> 15:03.708
last night after you
went to bed, um...

15:03.791 --> 15:06.000
I found a Flopsy Dog keychain,

15:06.083 --> 15:08.125
and one of the keys
said "staff apartments."

15:08.208 --> 15:11.541
Drew...do you live
in Merry Merry Land?

15:11.625 --> 15:13.625
- Okay, you know what?
You two are making fun of me,

15:13.708 --> 15:15.458
and I don't think
it's very funny.

15:15.541 --> 15:17.625
And Elliott,
I've asked you this before,

15:17.708 --> 15:20.791
but will you please stop
going through my bag?

15:20.875 --> 15:22.500
- Okay, Drew,
I'm not making fun!

15:22.583 --> 15:24.416
I'm literally just
putting two and two together.

15:24.500 --> 15:26.500
- Look, I'm gonna go ahead
and just say it, Drew,

15:26.583 --> 15:28.291
I think
you should've said "yes."

15:28.375 --> 15:30.333
She just seemed sweet,
you know what I mean?

15:30.416 --> 15:33.166
Unlike the person
that we are searching for,

15:33.250 --> 15:34.500
who is not sweet.

15:34.583 --> 15:36.083
And we just love you,
Drew-Boo.

15:36.166 --> 15:39.166
We just want you to be happy.
That's all.

15:39.250 --> 15:40.916
- Thank you.

15:46.791 --> 15:49.000
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

15:49.083 --> 15:50.458
- Chip?

15:50.541 --> 15:57.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:06.333 --> 16:08.458
[grunts]
- No, no, no, please!

16:08.541 --> 16:10.083
Please don't hurt me!
Please don't hurt me!

16:10.166 --> 16:11.625
- Chip, I'm not gonna hurt you!
- Please, please!

16:11.708 --> 16:13.166
- Stop it! Stop it!
- Please, please, please!

16:13.250 --> 16:15.083
- Okay! I swear
I'm not gonna hurt you!

16:15.166 --> 16:17.625
Stop! Stop squirming! Stop it!
- Oh, my God.

16:17.708 --> 16:19.166
- I want you...

16:20.291 --> 16:22.041
To do it again.

16:22.125 --> 16:23.625
- Do what?

16:25.541 --> 16:29.208
- Make me forget
everything that I've done.

16:29.291 --> 16:30.875
- Huh?

16:33.875 --> 16:35.916
- Make me be Stephanie.

16:36.875 --> 16:38.791
- Ma'am, think that's about it.

16:38.875 --> 16:40.875
- Every inch is soaked?

16:40.958 --> 16:43.416
- Uh, yeah.

16:43.500 --> 16:44.833
- Come and get it.

16:47.375 --> 16:49.625
100 for you.
100 for you.

16:49.708 --> 16:50.875
You didn't think I would really

16:50.958 --> 16:52.666
come through with this,
did you?

16:53.416 --> 16:55.083
Now, I'll see
if you've learned your lesson.

16:55.166 --> 16:57.000
There really are good people
in this world

16:57.083 --> 17:00.541
who mean what they say
and say what they mean.

17:01.958 --> 17:04.041
- You hurt me.

17:05.541 --> 17:08.166
You isolated me.

17:08.250 --> 17:10.750
You tortured me.

17:10.833 --> 17:12.208
But...

17:12.291 --> 17:14.375
it's still easier...

17:15.166 --> 17:17.291
To live with that anger...

17:18.375 --> 17:21.791
Than it is to live
with being myself.

17:25.166 --> 17:28.708
- And you want me
to make that hell go away?

17:30.500 --> 17:32.583
- I just wanna be free.

17:34.416 --> 17:36.625
But when I'm me...

17:36.708 --> 17:40.041
I can't escape being me.

17:42.958 --> 17:45.125
But when I'm someone else...

17:47.125 --> 17:48.666
I can just...

17:49.750 --> 17:51.416
I can just be.

17:54.541 --> 17:56.416
And that's what I want.

17:59.750 --> 18:02.416
I want to just...

18:02.500 --> 18:04.208
be.

18:04.708 --> 18:06.833
So, Chip...

18:06.916 --> 18:08.500
please, just...

18:08.583 --> 18:11.000
just make me someone
that I'm not.

18:18.750 --> 18:20.708
- You know what I hear?

18:22.375 --> 18:23.791
Whining.

18:24.583 --> 18:27.541
Whining that has nothing
to do with me.

18:29.208 --> 18:32.416
I did everything
that I did to you...

18:32.500 --> 18:34.625
because I wanted a friend.

18:35.833 --> 18:38.458
I needed one friend!

18:38.541 --> 18:40.500
But for one moment,

18:40.583 --> 18:43.833
I got to finally feel
what it's like...

18:43.916 --> 18:47.625
to be myself
around somebody else.

18:48.458 --> 18:51.041
And can you imagine
what it feels like

18:51.125 --> 18:52.708
for you to come in here

18:52.791 --> 18:55.041
and want to do it
all over again,

18:55.125 --> 18:58.666
but you could care less
about me or how I feel?

18:58.750 --> 19:00.208
- That's not true.

19:00.291 --> 19:01.416
Chip...

19:01.500 --> 19:03.833
we can still be friends.

19:03.916 --> 19:06.458
As long as you get
what you want...

19:07.250 --> 19:09.708
And I get what I want.

19:12.916 --> 19:15.416
- You think I know what I did?

19:15.500 --> 19:17.250
I don't know what I did!

19:17.333 --> 19:18.750
I bonked you on the head,

19:18.833 --> 19:21.708
I read half a book
and a couple articles

19:21.791 --> 19:24.041
and made up a drug cocktail

19:24.125 --> 19:27.875
out of pills that have been
in this house since the '80s!

19:28.000 --> 19:29.916
And the moon was full!

19:30.000 --> 19:32.375
Maybe it was that.
I don't know!

19:33.250 --> 19:36.625
I'm not some evil mastermind,
okay?

19:37.291 --> 19:39.791
I'm just wealthy and inbred.

19:41.375 --> 19:45.125
Oh, I'm inbred, by the way.
It's official.

19:45.916 --> 19:47.958
<i>- Chip, are you down there?</i>

19:48.041 --> 19:49.416
<i>We have to go.</i>

19:49.500 --> 19:51.666
- I'm coming!

19:56.500 --> 19:58.875
<i>- It's time, Chip, hurry up.</i>
<i>- I'm coming.</i>

19:58.958 --> 20:00.875
<i>- I know, but my sinuses</i>
<i>are killing me.</i>

20:00.958 --> 20:02.708
Those fumes.

20:02.791 --> 20:04.166
Oh!

20:05.125 --> 20:07.000
- Can Dory come, too?

20:08.166 --> 20:09.791
- That's the Dory girl!

20:09.875 --> 20:11.708
Well, of course, she can!

20:11.791 --> 20:14.000
Why don't you wait
in the car, sweetheart?

20:16.125 --> 20:17.916
Well, look at you.

20:18.000 --> 20:19.750
It's a bold haircut.

20:19.833 --> 20:20.791
Come on.

20:20.875 --> 20:23.083
Come on, there you go.

20:23.166 --> 20:25.416
I've been looking forward
to meeting you.

20:25.500 --> 20:26.916
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:27.000 --> 20:30.375
I've heard so much about you.

20:30.458 --> 20:33.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:33.791 --> 20:36.125
Ooh. Sorry, sweetheart.

20:36.208 --> 20:38.041
- [panting]

20:38.125 --> 20:39.458
- Well,
if it's any consolation,

20:39.541 --> 20:41.916
we are a very good family.

20:42.000 --> 20:45.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:45.500 --> 20:46.625
- Drewbie!

20:46.708 --> 20:48.750
Please do not be mad at me,
okay?

20:48.833 --> 20:51.458
I love you so much.
I just--I feel really bad.

20:51.541 --> 20:54.000
I shouldn't have said anything,
okay?

20:55.916 --> 20:57.625
- I'm not mad.

21:00.291 --> 21:01.833
[crying]
I'm just really

21:01.916 --> 21:03.833
disappointed in myself.

21:03.916 --> 21:06.166
- Drew!
- Drewbie!

21:06.250 --> 21:08.375
- I don't know who I am!

21:08.458 --> 21:09.583
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!
- Drewbie, Drewbie!

21:09.666 --> 21:10.916
- What's wrong? What's wrong?

21:11.000 --> 21:12.333
What's up, baby?
- Oh, sweetie!

21:12.416 --> 21:14.583
- Oh, God!
- Hey, it's okay, it's okay.

21:15.291 --> 21:17.000
- [crying]
I don't know where I belong!

21:17.083 --> 21:18.958
I don't know where to go!

21:19.041 --> 21:20.708
I don't know who to love!

21:20.791 --> 21:22.750
- That's okay.

21:22.833 --> 21:25.166
- She's so nice.

21:25.250 --> 21:27.666
Like, she's like
a really nice,

21:27.750 --> 21:30.208
beautiful princess.

21:31.583 --> 21:34.208
I can't love her
'cause I don't love myself!

21:35.458 --> 21:38.041
I've been finding out
more stuff about myself,

21:38.125 --> 21:39.875
and it's like
I don't like it!

21:39.958 --> 21:41.333
- I know, I know.

21:42.458 --> 21:44.708
- I killed a man!

21:44.791 --> 21:46.458
- [sobbing]

21:46.541 --> 21:50.208
I know!
I know!

21:50.291 --> 21:51.708
I know!
It's not good!

21:51.791 --> 21:55.416
Not--not you, not you, but me.
Me! Me!

21:55.500 --> 21:58.916
Look at me and my stupid,
fat choices!

21:59.000 --> 22:00.333
I'm just--I'm a person

22:00.416 --> 22:02.875
playing a person
playing a person!

22:02.958 --> 22:04.166
And it's all fear!

22:04.250 --> 22:06.375
It's all because of fear!
I mean...

22:06.458 --> 22:09.958
[voice breaking]
that factory blew up, you guys!

22:10.875 --> 22:12.250
- What factory?

22:12.333 --> 22:14.541
- The Elliott Guns factory!

22:14.625 --> 22:17.708
One gun went off,
and then another went off,

22:17.791 --> 22:20.625
and then another went off,
and then they all went off,

22:20.708 --> 22:23.208
and it was--they all just
went off like dominos,

22:23.291 --> 22:26.333
and then the walls
of the factory collapsed.

22:26.416 --> 22:27.666
Oh, God.

22:27.750 --> 22:30.708
And then--and then I sued
the building owners,

22:30.791 --> 22:32.291
saying it was an earthquake,

22:32.375 --> 22:35.416
and I'm gonna make "$2 million"
off of that?

22:35.500 --> 22:37.125
What the hell, man?

22:37.208 --> 22:38.625
What's my problem?

22:38.708 --> 22:40.958
I'm a fucking
despicable person!

22:41.041 --> 22:43.166
- [crying]
No, you're not!

22:43.250 --> 22:44.750
I am!
- No...

22:44.833 --> 22:46.125
- I am!
- No.

22:46.208 --> 22:47.750
- I signed up to do a movie

22:47.833 --> 22:50.541
that completely mocks
all my best friends,

22:50.625 --> 22:53.500
and I was so bad
that I got fired from it!

22:53.583 --> 22:55.708
- No, no.
- And everyone in the industry

22:55.791 --> 22:57.208
literally thinks I'm a joke,

22:57.291 --> 22:59.416
and I'm doing
all this self-help.

22:59.500 --> 23:03.291
I'm so exhausted trying to find
my fucking power!

23:03.375 --> 23:05.750
[sobbing]
Please just tell me who I am!

23:05.833 --> 23:07.166
I don't know who I...

23:07.250 --> 23:08.791
- Or any of us, okay?

23:08.875 --> 23:10.666
We're all so fucking lost.

23:10.750 --> 23:13.000
We're like a lost generation.

23:13.083 --> 23:15.000
- It's like we just have
to make a mockery

23:15.083 --> 23:16.875
of all our lives.

23:22.583 --> 23:24.791
- Look at us, you guys.

23:24.875 --> 23:27.708
We're literally sitting...

23:27.791 --> 23:29.458
on the side of the road

23:29.541 --> 23:32.958
looking for a friend
who screamed at us

23:33.041 --> 23:35.583
that she wants to kill us.

23:35.666 --> 23:38.916
Dory doesn't even want us
to look for her.

23:40.250 --> 23:41.666
- Well, that went well.

23:41.750 --> 23:43.250
We can call Big Jon
and tell him

23:43.333 --> 23:44.750
that he has one less job to do,

23:44.833 --> 23:46.833
and we'll save
a little bit of money.

23:46.916 --> 23:48.666
- [sighs]

23:48.750 --> 23:50.750
Couldn't we have just
paid her off?

23:50.833 --> 23:52.000
- [laughs] Oh, no.

23:52.083 --> 23:53.708
No, you went too far.

23:53.791 --> 23:56.250
You see, there's a line,
a pay line.

23:56.333 --> 23:59.083
You crossed over.
You crossed over the pay line.

24:00.666 --> 24:02.500
All right, you two, listen up.

24:02.583 --> 24:04.541
<i>[jazz music playing]</i>

24:04.625 --> 24:08.041
<i>- ♪ Ah, ah oh ♪</i>

24:08.125 --> 24:12.041
<i>♪ Kiss away ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Kiss away my tears ♪</i>

24:12.125 --> 24:15.875
<i>- ♪ Kiss away ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Kiss away my tears ♪</i>

24:15.958 --> 24:19.416
<i>- ♪ Kiss away ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Kiss away my tears ♪</i>

24:19.500 --> 24:23.708
<i>♪ Ah-ah ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ My tears ♪</i>

24:23.791 --> 24:26.458
<i>♪ Kiss away my tears ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Ah ♪</i>

24:26.541 --> 24:30.208
<i>♪ Ah, ah ♪</i>

24:30.291 --> 24:31.875
- Now, you wait
until we're out of sight,

24:31.958 --> 24:34.500
then you count to 100,
and then you can light up.

24:35.291 --> 24:37.208
But skedaddle away
really quickly

24:37.291 --> 24:39.333
so you don't get caught.

24:39.416 --> 24:41.375
Oh, and boys?

24:41.458 --> 24:43.250
Merry Christmas.

24:48.791 --> 24:50.750
- Do we try to save her?

24:55.666 --> 24:57.875
- It is almost Christmas.
- Thank you.

24:57.958 --> 24:59.916
- We should probably be,
like...

25:00.000 --> 25:01.333
with our families.

25:01.416 --> 25:03.375
- And just leave her here?

25:04.666 --> 25:06.083
It's Christmas.

25:06.166 --> 25:07.666
- I guess we have to save her.

25:07.750 --> 25:10.333
- But, but, but, but...

25:12.125 --> 25:13.416
Do we?

25:13.500 --> 25:14.708
- [panting]

25:14.791 --> 25:17.541
[lock beeping]

25:17.625 --> 25:19.166
[door buzzes]

25:26.708 --> 25:28.208
[door buzzes]

25:28.291 --> 25:29.458
- No.

25:29.541 --> 25:31.750
No! No, that's the code!

25:31.833 --> 25:33.791
That's the code!
That's the code!

25:33.875 --> 25:36.375
- Okay, of course,
I want to save Dory.

25:36.458 --> 25:39.208
We all want to save Dory.
- Yeah. Mm.

25:39.291 --> 25:41.625
- But maybe she doesn't need
to be saved right now.

25:41.708 --> 25:43.458
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

25:43.541 --> 25:45.333
You know what I'm saying?

25:45.416 --> 25:48.458
You cannot help someone
who doesn't want your help.

25:48.541 --> 25:50.083
- Help me!

25:50.166 --> 25:52.000
Help me!

25:52.083 --> 25:54.625
- Drew, what do you think?

25:56.125 --> 25:59.375
- I mean, I already ordered
a car to the train station.

26:00.666 --> 26:03.791
<i>[tense music]</i>

26:03.875 --> 26:06.833
[flames crackling]

26:06.916 --> 26:14.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:18.666 --> 26:19.958
[lock beeping]
[door buzzes]

26:20.041 --> 26:21.166
- [yells]

26:23.625 --> 26:24.916
[door buzzes]

26:30.041 --> 26:31.166
[screams]

26:34.916 --> 26:35.833
[gasps]

26:35.916 --> 26:37.958
[panting]

26:40.583 --> 26:41.750
[sirens wailing]

26:41.833 --> 26:42.833
- [groans]

26:42.916 --> 26:46.250
[wailing continues]

26:47.750 --> 26:48.791
- Ah!

26:48.875 --> 26:50.541
- Why do they make that
so loud?

26:50.625 --> 26:52.000
- [groans]
- I hate that so much.

26:52.083 --> 26:53.666
- I know,
it's so freaking annoying.

26:53.750 --> 26:55.166
It's like,
what are you guys doing?

26:55.250 --> 26:56.833
Getting a cat out of a tree
or something?

26:56.916 --> 26:58.291
- Can you believe we pay
for that?

26:58.375 --> 27:00.375
Out of our own tax dollars.

27:00.458 --> 27:07.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:14.500 --> 27:16.666
- What a day from hell.

27:20.208 --> 27:21.541
[knock on glass]
- Can you unlock it?

27:21.625 --> 27:22.666
all:
Thank you.

27:22.750 --> 27:29.916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:37.583 --> 27:38.791
- [gasps]

27:41.250 --> 27:42.458
[gasps]

27:42.541 --> 27:43.916
[coughs]

27:46.791 --> 27:47.916
[grunts]

27:49.125 --> 27:50.250
[grunts]

27:51.375 --> 27:52.500
[grunts]

27:53.375 --> 27:54.458
[grunts]

27:55.166 --> 27:56.375
[grunts]
[music stops]

28:08.166 --> 28:11.166
<i>[steady electronic music]</i>

28:11.250 --> 28:14.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:14.750 --> 28:17.625
[panting]

28:17.708 --> 28:24.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:52.541 --> 28:55.500
I'm just terrified
that there's this person,

28:55.583 --> 28:57.916
deep down inside of me, that...

28:58.000 --> 29:00.458
I don't fully understand...

29:00.541 --> 29:03.041
and that I cannot trust.

29:04.000 --> 29:06.125
I made all these things happen.

29:08.208 --> 29:11.041
<i>- ♪ I would never</i>
<i>trust my heart ♪</i>

29:11.125 --> 29:14.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:14.208 --> 29:16.000
<i>♪ I would say, I would say ♪</i>

29:16.083 --> 29:17.458
<i>♪ I would never tr-- ♪</i>

29:17.541 --> 29:20.750
<i>[flames crackling]</i>

29:26.041 --> 29:28.958
<i>[wood cracking]</i>

29:41.083 --> 29:44.916
<i>[flames continue crackling]</i>

29:53.708 --> 29:56.083
<i>[wood collapsing]</i>

30:00.416 --> 30:01.541
- [coughs]
